## Technical Gaps (Top 5)
1. **Dynamic Visual Rhythm**: The old video used static images. High-performing Shorts use 1.5-2s cuts and Ken Burns zooms.
2. **Typography & Layout**: Old video had screen-filling generic text. Needs bold, modern fonts with intentional placement (not blocking the product).
3. **POV & Authenticity**: Generic renders vs. hands-on/POV clips. Must use clips that show the product in action.
4. **Audio-Visual Sync (SFX)**: Old video lacked ASMR/impact SFX. Every action needs a corresponding sound (click, slice, pop).
5. **Color/Mood Grading**: Old video was flat. Needs professional grading (High contrast or Warm aesthetic) to look "expensive".

